CIDR- Represents the Network Bits 
In Class - A -> 1 network octet  -> 8 bits , Default CIDR of Class A /8 , If any thing more than 8 means subnetting is happened
In Class - B -> 2 network octets -> 16 bits, Default CIDR of Class B /16 , If any thing more than 16 means subnetting is happened
In Class - C -> 3 network octets -> 24 bits, Default CIDR of Class C /24 , If any thing more than 24 means subnetting is happened

Subnet Mask - Change the network bit to 255 and host bit to 0
Network ID- In the IP keep the Network bit as it is and change the host bit to 0
Broadcast ID - In the IP keep the Network bit as it is and change the host bit to 255

NO of usable IP address, Usable IPs=2^(number of host bits) âˆ’2
In -2 one is Network ID & the other is Broadcast ID 
The first address of a subnet = Network ID
The last address of a subnet = Broadcast Address

In Classs C 
